713
00:36:55.413 --> 00:36:56.991
and then we'll...
we'll find you a pump.

714
00:36:57.015 --> 00:36:59.985
- No. I can't... I can't give him formula.
- [Helen] Why not?

715
00:37:00.051 --> 00:37:03.283
Because it leads to a lifetime
of obesity and eating disorders.

716
00:37:03.354 --> 00:37:05.323
It's better to be
plump and civilized

717
00:37:05.390 --> 00:37:06.801
- than raised like a wolf cub.
- Okay.

718
00:37:06.825 --> 00:37:08.691
That's really enough
from you. okay?

719
00:37:08.760 --> 00:37:10.228
[crying continues]

720
00:37:10.295 --> 00:37:11.855
Sierra. when's the
last time you slept?

721
00:37:12.030 --> 00:37:15.364
I don't know. I... A day ago.
two days ago. I don't know.

722
00:37:15.433 --> 00:37:17.061
All right. Here's
what's gonna happen.

723
00:37:17.535 --> 00:37:19.613
You're gonna lie down in Stacey's
room and you're gonna go out

724
00:37:19.637 --> 00:37:20.997
and get some
formula and a bottle.

725
00:37:21.039 --> 00:37:22.667
- No. Helen.
- Yes. Sierra.

726
00:37:22.874 --> 00:37:25.002
One bottle is not
gonna do any harm.

727
00:37:25.076 --> 00:37:27.636
He needs to eat and you
need to sleep. So let's just...

728
00:37:28.413 --> 00:37:31.781
Let's just fix these problems right now
and then we'll sort out the rest. okay?

729
00:37:32.183 --> 00:37:33.776
- [exhales]
- [Eddie crying]

730
00:37:33.852 --> 00:37:35.529
Go. just go ahead;
it's right down the hall.

731
00:37:35.553 --> 00:37:37.146
- On your right.
- Okay. thank you.

732
00:37:37.222 --> 00:37:39.782
- Mm-hm.
- [Eddie crying]

733
00:37:42.560 --> 00:37:43.653
You. too. Go.

734
00:37:44.562 --> 00:37:47.088
- That woman is a child.
- I know.

735
00:37:49.901 --> 00:37:50.901
Hi.

736
00:37:51.503 --> 00:37:52.971
[door opens]

737
00:37:54.639 --> 00:37:55.663
- Okay.
- [door closes]

738
00:37:57.408 --> 00:37:59.240
- [cries]
- Ah. ah. ah. none of that.

739
00:37:59.310 --> 00:38:02.280
- [crying stops]
- Thank you.

740
00:38:03.181 --> 00:38:04.672
- [coos]
- Hmm.

741
00:38:13.792 --> 00:38:14.792
[softly] Nice work.

742
00:38:23.101 --> 00:38:24.899
You look just like your dad.

743
00:38:43.154 --> 00:38:47.285
[sighs]

744
00:39:07.979 --> 00:39:09.971
[man on TV chattering]

745
00:39:10.048 --> 00:39:12.745
- Don't you guys have homework?
- [Trevor] We'll do it later.

746
00:39:12.917 --> 00:39:14.408
[man on TV] <i>You
have not met him yet.</i>

747
00:39:15.253 --> 00:39:16.277
[man on TV chuckles]

748
00:39:17.322 --> 00:39:18.790
<i>Is that what you like?</i>

749
00:39:19.924 --> 00:39:22.519
- What is this. <i>The Maze?</i>
<i>- The Maze 2.</i>

750
00:39:22.827 --> 00:39:24.796
- This time. it's even more personal.
- [snickers]

751
00:39:24.863 --> 00:39:27.162
It's um. yeah. the sequel.

752
00:39:29.300 --> 00:39:31.428
- What?
- How was your date?

753
00:39:31.669 --> 00:39:32.880
- That you went on?
- Uh. sorry. you know.

754
00:39:32.904 --> 00:39:33.803
he thought putting this on

755
00:39:33.872 --> 00:39:35.883
- would make you talk about it.
- With Sasha mother-freaking Mann?

756
00:39:35.907 --> 00:39:37.170
I told him it was a dumb idea.

757
00:39:37.242 --> 00:39:38.519
It wasn't really
a date. you guys.

758
00:39:38.543 --> 00:39:39.636
What is he like?

759
00:39:39.711 --> 00:39:41.431
- Yeah. are you gonna see him again?
- Yeah.

760
00:39:41.613 --> 00:39:44.310
When can I start telling people
that Sasha Mann is your boyfriend?

761
00:39:44.382 --> 00:39:45.382
You can't.

762
00:39:45.483 --> 00:39:47.349
And you can't
tweet it or blog it

763
00:39:47.418 --> 00:39:48.863
- or any of that stuff.
- Don't worry. Mom. he won't.

764
00:39:48.887 --> 00:39:50.378
- It's a vlog. [chuckles]
- Okay.

765
00:39:50.655 --> 00:39:53.124
Anyway. I might be done
with boyfriends for a while.

766
00:39:53.224 --> 00:39:54.224
[Brooklyn] What?

767
00:39:55.460 --> 00:39:58.259
Well. I've had my share.
They can be exhausting.

768
00:39:58.329 --> 00:40:01.299
I mean. do what you want.
but you are way too hot

769
00:40:01.366 --> 00:40:03.767
- not to have any more boyfriends.
- Gross.

770
00:40:03.835 --> 00:40:04.979
- That's my mom.
- I'm serious.

771
00:40:05.003 --> 00:40:06.096
[Trevor] Stop.

772
00:40:06.371 --> 00:40:07.395
[indistinct chatter]

773
00:40:07.472 --> 00:40:09.464
[phone ringing]

774
00:40:18.149 --> 00:40:19.879
- Hello?
- [Sasha] <i>Hi.</i>

775
00:40:19.951 --> 00:40:20.951
[Sasha on TV] <i>Hi.</i>

776
00:40:21.819 --> 00:40:22.819
Hi.

777
00:40:23.721 --> 00:40:26.782
Uh. uh. how's it
going. Sasha... Mann?

778
00:40:26.858 --> 00:40:28.793
[Sash on phone] <i>What
are you doing right now?</i>

779
00:40:28.860 --> 00:40:31.557
Uh. I'm at home. Why?

780
00:40:31.629 --> 00:40:34.758
<i>Well. the thing is. uh. ever
since you came to my place</i>

781
00:40:34.832 --> 00:40:39.236
<i>and-and we spent that evening together.
I can't stop thinking about my furniture.</i>

782
00:40:39.304 --> 00:40:40.499
Your furniture?

783
00:40:40.805 --> 00:40:43.104
<i>Yeah. I can't get
it out of my head.</i>

784
00:40:43.374 --> 00:40:46.367
<i>I think you're right.
uh. I need more stuff.</i>

785
00:40:46.577 --> 00:40:49.604
<i>I was hoping you'd come by set
and help me make some decisions.</i>

786
00:40:49.681 --> 00:40:51.309
<i>If-if you're not
too busy. that is.</i>

787
00:40:51.382 --> 00:40:52.816
I know you have it on your mind.

788
00:40:52.884 --> 00:40:55.479
You remember how lovely the
summers are out there. Don't you?

789
00:40:55.553 --> 00:40:57.698
<i>- Helen. are you there?</i>
- Um. I have to deal with something here.

790
00:40:57.722 --> 00:40:58.722
I'll call you back.

791
00:40:59.457 --> 00:41:02.950
They've got a great high school there.
Bridgehampton High. Huge building.

792
00:41:03.027 --> 00:41:04.707
- Very...
- Can I talk to you for a second?

793
00:41:10.001 --> 00:41:11.912
What are you doing? Are
you telling him we're moving?

794
00:41:11.936 --> 00:41:14.462
- I'm just laying the groundwork.
- Please don't do that.

795
00:41:14.706 --> 00:41:17.608
Helen. you can't uproot
them like you did last time.

796
00:41:17.675 --> 00:41:19.371
It's not healthy.

797
00:41:19.610 --> 00:41:22.842
Children have to be
prepared for traumatic events.

798
00:41:22.914 --> 00:41:25.611
I think what we should
do tonight at dinner

799
00:41:25.683 --> 00:41:28.175
is talk about the East Coast
in a general kind of way.

800
00:41:28.252 --> 00:41:30.118
You should say how
much you miss it.

801
00:41:30.188 --> 00:41:31.486
I'll mention how glorious it is

802
00:41:31.556 --> 00:41:33.149
- this time of year.
- I'm going out.

803
00:41:40.098 --> 00:41:42.397
- [knocking]
- [Sasha] Yeah? Come on in.

804
00:41:46.904 --> 00:41:48.668
Oh. you came.

805
00:41:49.374 --> 00:41:50.374
I wasn't sure you would.

806
00:41:50.441 --> 00:41:54.003
Uh. yeah. I'm sorry. I
have... things going on.

807
00:41:54.078 --> 00:41:56.206
- I really appreciate you making time.
- Yeah.

808
00:41:58.216 --> 00:41:59.216
Please come on in.

809
00:41:59.650 --> 00:42:00.650
Sit down.

810
00:42:01.853 --> 00:42:03.412
- Um...
- [sighs]

811
00:42:03.488 --> 00:42:05.889
So you need some help
making some decisions?

812
00:42:05.957 --> 00:42:07.687
Yeah. um...

813
00:42:08.493 --> 00:42:09.620
thing is.

814
00:42:09.994 --> 00:42:13.260
I moved to Malibu
because I was grieving

815
00:42:13.331 --> 00:42:15.051
and I just needed to
get away from the world

816
00:42:15.099 --> 00:42:17.796
and I thought if I have nothing.

817
00:42:18.002 --> 00:42:19.937
then I'll have
nothing to lose. right?

818
00:42:20.838 --> 00:42:23.273
But then the other
night. uh. after you left.

819
00:42:23.341 --> 00:42:25.435
I realized that time
in my life is over.

820
00:42:25.510 --> 00:42:28.810
It's passed and I don't need
to live like a monk anymore

821
00:42:28.880 --> 00:42:29.880
to keep order in my head.

822
00:42:29.981 --> 00:42:33.884
I want to feel things again.
So I took you very seriously.

823
00:42:34.052 --> 00:42:35.782
And I hired a professional.

824
00:42:36.454 --> 00:42:38.923
Um. supposedly...

825
00:42:39.624 --> 00:42:43.288
one of the best interior
designers in all of Hollywood.

826
00:42:43.361 --> 00:42:45.262
- Um...
- The trouble is. look.

827
00:42:45.930 --> 00:42:47.762
I really don't like it.

828
00:42:49.934 --> 00:42:50.934
No. I see what you mean.

829
00:42:50.968 --> 00:42:52.679
- It's totally not what I expected.
- It's chaotic.

830
00:42:52.703 --> 00:42:54.365
Yes. it is.

831
00:42:54.672 --> 00:42:56.231
- Um...
- It's too much.

832
00:42:56.407 --> 00:42:57.739
I was thinking...

833
00:42:57.942 --> 00:43:01.208
just. you know.
things with really clean.

834
00:43:01.279 --> 00:43:03.373
simple lines. like a modern
area rug there. maybe.

835
00:43:03.448 --> 00:43:06.680
or. um. or a Noguchi lamp there.

836
00:43:11.522 --> 00:43:14.981
- What?
- I just had the most brilliant idea.

837
00:43:16.127 --> 00:43:19.529
- Why don't you do it?
- What? No.

838
00:43:20.198 --> 00:43:22.376
Well. you know what you like
and you obviously have great taste.

839
00:43:22.400 --> 00:43:25.928
Yeah. but I don't... I have...
I don't... I have... I'm... My...

840
00:43:26.504 --> 00:43:28.735
And we'd get to spend
a lot of time together.

841
00:43:31.776 --> 00:43:32.776
[whispering] Yeah.

842
00:43:34.345 --> 00:43:35.745
But why?

843
00:43:36.147 --> 00:43:39.914
- [chuckles] What do you mean. why?
- I mean. there are tons of women.

844
00:43:39.984 --> 00:43:41.543
I'm sure you have tons of women.

845
00:43:41.619 --> 00:43:45.556
You know. famous women.
younger women. taller women

846
00:43:45.623 --> 00:43:47.057
that you-you can... You're...

847
00:43:47.125 --> 00:43:49.720
I'm having a very difficult
time believing that I'm your type.

848
00:43:49.861 --> 00:43:53.320
Uh. that's probably because you don't
have the faintest idea what my type is

849
00:43:53.631 --> 00:43:57.466
because you categorically
refuse to give me a chance.

850
00:44:00.104 --> 00:44:01.572
- [knock on door]
- Yes?

851
00:44:01.639 --> 00:44:04.473
- [woman] Mr. Mann? They need you on set.
- Just a second. please.

852
00:44:05.376 --> 00:44:09.143
Um. listen. I'm taking
everybody out tonight

853
00:44:09.213 --> 00:44:10.909
for karaoke and drinks.

854
00:44:10.982 --> 00:44:13.417
Why don't you come.
and we can discuss this...

855
00:44:13.484 --> 00:44:14.484
Okay.

856
00:44:15.620 --> 00:44:18.590
- Really?
- [laughs] Yes.

857
00:44:26.030 --> 00:44:27.030
[Noah] Helen.

858
00:44:28.132 --> 00:44:29.566
Oh. um. hi.

859
00:44:29.634 --> 00:44:32.695
It's... Actually. it's great you're
here. I was... I was about to call you.

860
00:44:32.770 --> 00:44:35.370
You really need to talk to Whitney
about this whole wedding thing.

861
00:44:35.540 --> 00:44:37.736
Um. uh. okay. What about it?

862
00:44:37.942 --> 00:44:41.071
[stammering] Well. this kid.
he's using her for a green card.

863
00:44:41.212 --> 00:44:43.252
- He doesn't work. he doesn't...
- I don't think so.

864
00:44:43.314 --> 00:44:44.839
I mean. I think he loves her.

865
00:44:44.916 --> 00:44:46.782
No. It's too fast.
and she is too young.

866
00:44:46.984 --> 00:44:49.317
And we're her parents.
We need to protect her.

867
00:44:49.387 --> 00:44:50.855
Uh. protect her from what?

868
00:44:50.922 --> 00:44:52.356
From making a big mistake.

869
00:44:52.623 --> 00:44:54.922
You want me to tell her
to call off her wedding?

870
00:44:54.992 --> 00:44:56.620
Yeah. I think you should.

871
00:44:58.529 --> 00:44:59.588
Why don't you do it?

872
00:44:59.730 --> 00:45:01.892
Because she doesn't listen
to me. She listens to you.

873
00:45:01.966 --> 00:45:05.528
- [Lisa] Rehearsal's up!
- Oh. Fuck. they need me for rehearsals.

874
00:45:05.603 --> 00:45:06.603
Will you talk to her?

875
00:45:06.771 --> 00:45:08.763
Uh... yeah. sure.

876
00:45:08.973 --> 00:45:12.239
Okay. thanks. Thanks for
coming. It's really good of you.

877
00:45:21.052 --> 00:45:22.543
- [Sasha] Hey.
- Hi.

878
00:45:22.920 --> 00:45:24.616
- Hey.
- You're finished already.

879
00:45:24.689 --> 00:45:26.749
Yes. Done for the day.

880
00:45:26.958 --> 00:45:29.928
Um. can we have
two Negronis. please?

881
00:45:29.994 --> 00:45:32.225
And keep it open. A
lot of people coming.

882
00:45:34.432 --> 00:45:35.432
[sighs]

883
00:45:36.667 --> 00:45:38.135
- So...
- So...

884
00:45:38.202 --> 00:45:39.568
Have you thought about it?

885
00:45:40.638 --> 00:45:41.503
About what?

886
00:45:41.639 --> 00:45:42.732
Designing my house.

887
00:45:42.807 --> 00:45:45.333
[scoffs] I can't design
your house. Sasha.

888
00:45:45.409 --> 00:45:48.277
- Why the hell not?
- Because I have too much going on.

889
00:45:48.346 --> 00:45:51.145
- Like what?
- Like what?

890
00:45:51.215 --> 00:45:52.274
Yes. like what?

891
00:45:52.350 --> 00:45:54.581
Like I just found out my
father has Alzheimer's.

892
00:45:54.785 --> 00:45:56.686
- And?
- And he's completely ruined

893
00:45:56.754 --> 00:45:58.985
- the family's finances.
- Poor you.

894
00:45:59.223 --> 00:46:01.749
My mother is a crazy.
narcissistic bitch.

895
00:46:02.026 --> 00:46:03.460
- Big deal.
- And my neighbor...

896
00:46:03.527 --> 00:46:05.689
- Mm-hm.
- Had a one-night stand

897
00:46:05.763 --> 00:46:07.163
with my boyfriend who died.

898
00:46:07.331 --> 00:46:08.331
[chuckles]

899
00:46:08.833 --> 00:46:09.926
Sorry. that's not funny.

900
00:46:10.001 --> 00:46:11.526
- No.
- No. Now she has his baby.

901
00:46:11.602 --> 00:46:13.013
and she wants me
to take care of it.

902
00:46:13.037 --> 00:46:16.337
And I already have four kids of my
own. the oldest of whom is getting married.

903
00:46:16.407 --> 00:46:18.842
and Noah wants me to convince
her to call off the wedding.

904
00:46:18.909 --> 00:46:20.138
- Why?
- Because. I don't know.

905
00:46:20.211 --> 00:46:21.304
he doesn't like the guy.

906
00:46:21.379 --> 00:46:22.689
Why doesn't Noah
just talk to her himself?

907
00:46:22.713 --> 00:46:25.979
Because they don't have
that kind of relationship.

908
00:46:26.183 --> 00:46:29.381
Helen. you don't have
to set yourself on fire

909
00:46:29.453 --> 00:46:31.285
to keep other people warm.

910
00:46:35.159 --> 00:46:38.459
- I'm not really sure what that means.
- You are allowed to say no.

911
00:46:38.929 --> 00:46:41.694
- Okay. No. I won't design your house.
- Oh. no. no. no. not to me.

912
00:46:42.800 --> 00:46:44.166
- Do you like gin?
- No.

913
00:46:44.235 --> 00:46:46.101
- Of course you do.
- [laughs]

914
00:46:46.170 --> 00:46:47.729
- Cheers.
- Thank you.

915
00:46:50.975 --> 00:46:51.999
Thank you.

916
00:46:53.644 --> 00:46:55.704
- Can I ask you a question?
- Yeah. anything.

917
00:46:55.913 --> 00:46:59.315
Except if I'm in love
with you. That's a secret.

918
00:47:04.255 --> 00:47:06.690
Uh. who did you lose?

919
00:47:08.292 --> 00:47:09.851
You said you were grieving.

920
00:47:11.929 --> 00:47:14.023
You really don't know
anything about me. do you?

921
00:47:16.200 --> 00:47:17.224
Not so much.

922
00:47:17.301 --> 00:47:20.237
- You don't read the tabloids?
- Not since Noah went to prison.

923
00:47:21.739 --> 00:47:24.174
Um. her name was Lily.

924
00:47:24.375 --> 00:47:27.072
and she was my
fiancée. and. um...

925
00:47:29.914 --> 00:47:32.076
We met as kids. and
we'd come up together.

926
00:47:32.149 --> 00:47:35.244
And. well. my success
was awful for her.

927
00:47:35.319 --> 00:47:37.788
I didn't handle it well.
and she felt abandoned.

928
00:47:37.855 --> 00:47:39.585
And as I started working more.

929
00:47:39.657 --> 00:47:42.821
she started using more

930
00:47:43.361 --> 00:47:45.853
until. um...

931
00:47:47.998 --> 00:47:49.899
until she overdosed one day...

932
00:47:51.135 --> 00:47:52.135
in our car.

933
00:47:52.903 --> 00:47:54.838
And I was the one who found her.

934
00:47:55.072 --> 00:47:57.041
The newspapers reported
it as a suicide. so...

935
00:47:57.108 --> 00:47:58.108
[Noah] Hey.

936
00:47:59.543 --> 00:48:00.374
Hey.

937
00:48:00.444 --> 00:48:01.969
- Hi.
- Hi.

938
00:48:02.580 --> 00:48:03.580
Good of you to join us.

939
00:48:03.948 --> 00:48:06.349
Yeah. thanks for doing
this. It's a cute idea.

940
00:48:07.752 --> 00:48:09.015
- Something wrong?
- Yeah.

941
00:48:09.253 --> 00:48:12.849
Yeah. something is wrong. Sasha.
I just. uh. got a call from my agents.

942
00:48:12.923 --> 00:48:15.483
They said you told the
studio that you want to...

943
00:48:15.659 --> 00:48:17.127
you want to rewrite the script.

944
00:48:18.863 --> 00:48:21.059
That's not exactly what I said.

945
00:48:21.132 --> 00:48:22.909
but I actually tried to
talk to you about this...

946
00:48:22.933 --> 00:48:25.835
Yeah. well. you got my fucking
attention now. so what's the problem?

947
00:48:26.771 --> 00:48:29.049
Do you think we should do this
somewhere a bit more private. perhaps?

948
00:48:29.073 --> 00:48:30.473
Lead the way. Maestro.

949
